>Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2021-06-02\" who=\"#AR\">edited text division\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2026-01-18\" who=\"#OC\">tagged names and persons\u003C/change>\n            \u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\u003Csurface/>\u003C!-- \n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001094_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001094.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface> -->\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#AR\" source=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> καισαρ\u003Cgap reason=\"illegible\" quantity=\"1\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">α\u003C/supplied>υτοκρα\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>ου σεβα\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>σεπτικ\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"5\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>στραν κα\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"6\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003Cgap reason=\"illegible\" quantity=\"1\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>\u003Cw part=\"I\">Φλαουιο\u003C/w>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\u003C/name>\u003C/persName>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\n                        \u003Cnote>text of IG\u003C/note>\n                    \u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>The text is described as very lightly inscribed, and Kaibel is sceptical of its genuineness, since other stones which he saw in the collection of Lipari were false. Manganaro follows Kaibel's suggested conjectures, with the naming of an Emperor and filiation in the opening lines, suggested to be in the genitive preceded by ὑπὲρ σωτηρίας (for the safety of), and the benefactor being a Septic[ius], perhaps responsible for the construction of a [palae]stran, with a second individual, a Flavius, also involved.\n                    \u003C!--a frag.; some question of authenticity; Kaibel is dubious, but suggests some restorations, making this a dedication to Tiberius, although he notes that the names Septimius and Flavius do not fit that very well; at line 5 there appears to be mention of either a palaestra or an orchestra. Wilson cites it as possible evidence for a palaestra in Lilybaeum, while noting the problem of uncertain restoration.-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IG\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Kaibel\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1890\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>\n                            \u003Cref target=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\">275\u003C/ref>\n                        \u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Manganaro\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1988\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>45\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/RZSFKACR\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Wilson\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1990\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>169, 381 n.72\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/VF9MMBI9\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
